INSTRUCTIONS FOR USE:
1. Replace all [PLACEHOLDER] text with actual project data
2. Delete sections not applicable to your report type
3. Update metrics from your project tracking tools
4. Keep formatting consistent across all reports
5. Use color coding: 🔴 Red (critical) 🟡 Yellow (caution) 🟢 Green (good)
6. Tailor detail level to audience:
   - Executive: Keep to 1-2 pages, high-level only
   - Management: 3-4 pages, include trends
   - Team: Full detail, all sections
7. Include visuals where possible (charts, graphs)
8. Be honest about status - transparency builds trust
9. Focus on actionable information and decisions needed
10. Proofread before sending - typos damage credibility
